caption><p>(A) Representative PCR of DNA extracted from tail clips from weaned pups. Image shows wild-type, heterozygous (het), and APJ knockout (<sup>&#x02212;/&#x02212;</sup>) genotypes. DNA was isolated from tail tips and three reactions carried out for each sample: a, primers 1 and 2 to detect endogenous APJ; b, primers 3 and 4 to detect recombinant allele; and c, primers 5, 6, and 7 a multiplex reaction to detect both endogenous and targeted genes. (B) Comparable histology (H&#x00026;E) in sections of pituitary gland, adrenal gland, kidney, and lung of wild-type and APJ<sup>&#x02212;/&#x02212;</sup> mice. Scale bars=500&#x0200a;&#x003bc;m; a, anterior pituitary; c, cortex; i, intermediate lobe of pituitary; m, medulla; p, posterior pituitary. (C) Representative ISHH autoradiographic images showing <italic>APJ</italic> mRNA expression in sections of heart and PVN from wild-type ((i) and (iv)) and APJ<sup>&#x02212;/&#x02212;</sup> ((ii) and (v)) mice. No <italic>APJ</italic> mRNA expression was observed in the APJ<sup>&#x02212;/&#x02212;</sup> mice. No specific labeling was seen in the wild-type control heart section using a <sup>35</sup>S-labeled sense-strand RNA control probe (iii). a, atria; v, ventricle; 3V, third ventricle.</p></caption><graphic xlink:href="JOE090134f01"/></fig><fig id="fig2" position="float"><label>Figure 2</label><caption><p>Fluid homeostasis in water replete wild-type (filled bars) and APJ<sup>&#x02212;/&#x02212;</sup> (open bars) mice. Drinking behaviour (A) was significantly attenuated in APJ<sup>&#x02212;/&#x02212;</sup> mice compared with wild-type when measured over 24&#x0200a;h, however, neither urine volume (B) nor urine osmolality (C) differed between the genotypes. Data are mean&#x000b1;<sc>s.e.m.</sc>, <italic>n</italic>=16, results of <italic>t</italic>-test *<italic>P</italic>&#x0003c;0&#x000b7;5.</p></caption><graphic xlink:href="JOE090134f02"/></fig><fig id="fig3" position="float"><label>Figure 3</label><caption><p>Effects of water deprivation on urine volume and urine osmolality. Mice were housed in metabolic cages and urine volume collected after 24&#x0200a;h with water (WR) followed by 24&#x0200a;h without water (WD). (A) WD significantly decreased spontaneously voided urine volume in wild-type (solid line) but not APJ<sup>&#x02212;/&#x02212;</sup> (dotted line) mice compared with WR. (B) WD significantly increased urine osmolality in wild-type (solid line) but not APJ<sup>&#x02212;/&#x02212;</sup> (dotted line) mice. Data are mean&#x000b1;<sc>s.e.m.</sc>, <italic>n</italic>=8, results of two-way repeated measures ANOVA with Bonferroni <italic>post hoc</italic> test, ns, not significant; <sup>+</sup><italic>P</italic>&#x0003c;0&#x000b7;05, <sup>++</sup><italic>P</italic>&#x0003c;0&#x000b7;01 WD versus WR.</p></caption><graphic xlink:href="JOE090134f03"/></fig><fig id="fig4" position="float"><label>Figure 4</label><caption><p>Plasma arginine vasopressin (AVP) concentration in wild-type (filled bars) and APJ<sup>&#x02212;/&#x02212;</sup> (open bars) water replete (WR 24) mice and water deprived (WD 24) for 24&#x0200a;h. Data are mean&#x000b1;<sc>s.e.m.</sc>, <italic>n</italic>=6&#x02013;8, results of two-way ANOVA show significant comparable increases in both genotypes following water deprivation (<italic>P</italic>&#x0003c;0&#x000b7;001).</p></caption><graphic xlink:href="JOE090134f04"/></fig><fig id="fig5" position="float"><label>Figure 5</label><caption><p>Effect of water deprivation (WD) on expression of c-<italic>fos</italic> mRNA in the MnPO, SFO, SON, and PVN. Expression of c-<italic>fos</italic> mRNA was negligible in water replete (WR) wild-type (filled bars) and APJ<sup>&#x02212;/&#x02212;</sup> (open bars) mice. WD caused comparable increases in c-<italic>fos</italic> mRNA in the MnPO and SON of wild-type and APJ<sup>&#x02212;/&#x02212;</sup> mice, however, the WD-induced significant increase in c-<italic>fos</italic> mRNA expression was significantly reduced in the SFO of APJ<sup>&#x02212;/&#x02212;</sup> mice compared with wild-type, while in the PVN c-<italic>fos</italic> expression was accentuated in APJ<sup>&#x02212;/&#x02212;</sup> mice. The graph shows expression of c-<italic>fos</italic> mRNA calculated as a percentage of wild-type/WR in the MnPO (<italic>n</italic>=3), SFO (<italic>n</italic>=3), SON (<italic>n</italic>=4&#x02013;5), and PVN (<italic>n</italic>=4&#x02013;6). Data are mean&#x000b1;<sc>s.e.m.</sc> of 2&#x02013;4 images per animal and were analyzed using two-way ANOVA and Bonferroni <italic>post hoc</italic> tests: *<italic>P</italic>&#x0003c;0&#x000b7;05, ***<italic>P</italic>&#x0003c;0&#x000b7;001 wild-type versus APJ<sup>&#x02212;/&#x02212;</sup>; <sup>++</sup><italic>P</italic>&#x0003c;0&#x000b7;01, <sup>+++</sup><italic>P</italic>&#x0003c;0&#x000b7;001 WR versus WD.</p></caption><graphic xlink:href="JOE090134f05"/></fig><fig id="fig6" position="float"><label>Figure 6</label><caption><p>Expression of arginine vasopressin (<italic>AVP</italic>) mRNA in the PVN and SON of wild-type (filled bars) and APJ<sup>&#x02212;/&#x02212;</sup> (open bars) mice housed in metabolic cages with (WR) or without (WD) free access to drinking water for 24&#x0200a;h. The graph shows expression of <italic>AVP</italic> mRNA calculated as a percentage of wild-type/WR in the SON (<italic>n</italic>=4&#x02013;5) and PVN (<italic>n</italic>=4). Data are mean&#x000b1;<sc>s.e.m.</sc> of 2&#x02013;4 images per animal, result of <italic>t</italic>-test to compare basal <italic>AVP</italic> mRNA expression *<italic>P</italic>&#x0003c;0&#x000b7;05; comparisons between genotypes and treatment groups were made using two-way ANOVA and Bonferroni <italic>post hoc</italic> test, <sup>+</sup><italic>P</italic>&#x0003c;0&#x000b7;05, <sup>++</sup><italic>P</italic>&#x0003c;0&#x000b7;01, <sup>+++</sup><italic>P</italic>&#x0003c;0&#x000b7;001 WR versus WD.</p></caption><graphic xlink:href="JOE090134f06"/></fig></floats-group></article>